 :tx/rationale "THE INQUIRY ENGINE THESIS: Braid is not a categorization engine. It is an inquiry engine. The output is not 'this observation belongs to concept X.' The output is 'here is where my model disagrees with your observation — what does that mean?' Every iteration this session (threshold tuning, sigmoid, Otsu, online calibration) optimized classification. But the agent does not care which bin an observation goes in. The agent cares about what to do next. And what to do next comes from DISAGREEMENT between the system's model and the agent's observation. The concept centroid IS a hypothesis — a prediction that observations in this region will look like THIS. When an observation diverges, the centroid was wrong. The discrepancy vector (observation - centroid) encodes what was new. Braid's value proposition is knowledge CONFRONTATION, not knowledge management. The system earns its existence every time it shows the agent something that contradicts their current understanding. Traces to: ADR-FOUNDATION-014 (convergence thesis: reduce discrepancy), ADR-FOUNDATION-025 (acquisition function: highest alpha at maximum discrepancy), ADR-FOUNDATION-030 (free energy: minimize surprise by finding it first)."
